<DOC><DOCNO> AP890117-0105 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-17-89 1252EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a PM-BentsenFatherKilled 1stLd-Writethru a0569 01-17 0344</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bentsen Father Killed, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0569,0350</SECOND><HEAD>Senator's Father Killed In Auto Accident</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: SUBS 5th graf, `According to ...,' to clarify that intersectionhad a stop sign</HEAD><DATELINE>EDINBURG, Texas (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Lloyd Bentsen Sr., the father of Sen.Lloyd Bentsen, was killed in a traffic accident near this southTexas town this morning, police said. He was 92.   The senior Bentsen was killed when his car collided with anothercar at a rural intersection between Edinburg and Mission, aneighboring town just north of the Mexican border, said police ChiefA.C. Gonzales.   Bentsen's ranch, the Arrowhead, is about 30 miles northwest ofthe intersection.   Two people in the second car were injured, neither critically.   According to David Wells, a spokesman for the Texas Department ofPublic Safety, the accident occurred when Bentsen failed to yieldthe right of way at the intersection. Bentsen had a stop sign; theother car did not, Wells said.   ``I do not know if he stopped and then pulled out in front ofthis oncoming vehicle or didn't stop,'' Wells said.   Wells said Bentsen was pronounced dead at the scene by MissionJustice of the Peace Juan Rosel.   The occupants of the second car were identified as driver RamiroRosales and his sister, Margarita Rosales. Both taken to MissionHospital in McAllen, where Ms. Rosales was listed in stablecondition pending surgery; her brother was scheduled to be releasedafter treatment for cuts and bruises.   Bentsen managed about 42,000 acres of farms and six ranchesscattered over a south Texas empire he started carving out of thebrush and thorn forest in 1920.   He and his wife Dolly, who died in 1977, had three otherchildren: Kenneth, a Houston architect; Don, a McAllen businessman;and Betty, the wife of Rio Grande Valley businessman Dan Winn.   Lloyd Bentsen Jr. won re-election to his U.S. Senate seat lastNovember, when he also lost a run for vice president on theDemocratic ticket with Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis.   His office in Washington declined to comment on reports of thedeath.</TEXT></DOC>